Aspirin sales jumped 41 percent for a few weeks

earlier this year, not because of a rash of headaches.
With the treatment, the figure dropped to 8 percent.
Heart disease is the nation's leading cause of death, by far.
The usual cause of heart attacks is a blockage of the coronary arteries, which supply the heart muscle with oxygen-rich blood.
But that is beginning to change.
Much can be done to prevent heart attacks, great improvements are being made in treatments, and recovery is faster than ever before.
The use of a clot-dissolver and aspirin could, alone, save 25,000 lives a year in the United States, doctors say.
